w-z&=w+10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta

\\

\implies

|w-z|^2&=w\overline w+10^2\text{e}^\text{i}\theta \overline{\text{e}^\text{i}\theta}+10w\text{e}^\text{i}\theta+10\overline w\text{e}^\text{i}-10|w ,

\end{aligned}$$

and, using $\overline a\overline b=\overline{ab},$ $$\begin{aligned}

0&=w-z\overline{w-z}

\\

&=w\overline w+100\text{e}^\text{i}\theta \overline{\text{e}}^\text{i}\theta+10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta w+10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta \overline w-10w

\\

&=w\overline w+100+10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta (w+\overline w)-10w ,\text{ so}

\\

&=1+10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta\left(\frac{w+\overline w}{2}\right)-10w,\text{ by definition, }\Omega(\theta)=\frac{w+\overline w}{2},\text{ real number}

\\

&=1+10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta\Omega(\theta)-10w.

\end{aligned}$$

So $$0 =\begin{aligned}

1+\text{e}^\text{i}\theta\Omega(\theta)^2+\text{e}^\text{i}\theta\Omega(\theta)-10\text{e}^\text{i}\theta w,\text{ so as }\epsilon\text{'s values not 0 nor }1,

|w|=1,\text{ require }\Omega(\theta)=10\text{ at max},\text{ motive: to avoid divide by zero issue in second equation.

}\\

&=16,\text{ giving }8\text{ is sq root }

\end{aligned}$$

So we see, $$|z|=10\cos(\theta) = 10^\frac12 \text{ is our max }\Omega(\theta).$$ Hence, $$\frac{\Omega(\theta)}{ |z|} = \frac{8{{}}}{10}=0.8.$$

